A
UNIFYING
THEORY
OF
HIGH
LATITUDE
GEOPHYSICAL
PHENOMENA
AND
GEOMAGNETIC
STORMS
A
CONVECTION
SYSTEM
SET
UP
IN
THE
MAGNETOSPHERE
BY
VISCOUS
INTERACTION
BETWEEN
THE
MAGNETOSPHERE
AND
A
SOLAR
WIND
OR
BY
OTHER
SOURCES
COULD
ACCOUNT
FOR
A
WIDE
VARIETY
OF
OBSERVED
HIGH
LATITUDE
GEOPHYSICAL
PHENOMENA
AND
STORM
TIME
VARIATIONS
